  "prompt": "Do I really need to buy tires in pairs?",
  "response": "While it's not always strictly necessary to buy tires in pairs, it is generally recommended for several reasons:\n\n1. Balanced handling: Matching tires ensure even traction and handling, which is crucial for vehicle safety.\n\n2. Consistent performance: Tires with different tread depths and wear patterns can affect your car's stability and braking.\n\n3. Drivetrain stress: Uneven tires can put additional stress on your vehicle's suspension and drivetrain.\n\nHowever, there are some specific situations where you might not need to buy pairs:\n\n- If only one tire is damaged and the others are in good condition\n- If your vehicle is all-wheel drive, you may need to replace all four tires\n- If you're replacing run-flat or special performance tires\n\nIf you can only afford to replace one tire, try to match it as closely as possible to the existing tire in terms of brand, model, and tread depth. Consult a professional mechanic for the best advice specific to your vehicle.",
